  "text": "For calibration purposes, there are two major modes of display which determine what types of technical issues that need to be addressed: (i) video seethrough HMD systems and (ii) optical see-through HMD systems. The calibration issues in a video seethrough HMD system are described in detail elsewhere [CITATION_1] . We define an optical see-through HMD system as the combination of an optical see-through HMD and a person's eyes.",
  "correct_citation": {
